										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>GIM Raises US$20 Million to Expand AI Investment Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Grace Investment Machine (GIM), an AI-native investment technology company, has raised US$20 million in Series A funding. The round was co-led by Hony Capital and a leading US venture capital firm. Existing investors Monolith Capital and IDG Capital also participated.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment marks GIM&#8217;s third funding round within its first year of operations. The company plans to use the new capital to expand its operations, strengthen product development and accelerate research into agentic artificial intelligence for capital markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">GIM is focused on building intelligent systems that move beyond traditional investment research tools. Instead of simply organising information, its technology independently creates, evaluates and refines investment ideas using real-time market data and continuous feedback.</span></p>
<h2><b>Agentic AI Aims to Transform Investment Decision-Making<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203463" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203463" class="size-full wp-image-203463" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-in-a-vibrant-neon-cy_lo-auiqBXiKmPYlptnUN4w_MDrI5zQKQ5yLCTtlV7Smyw.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI systems autonomously generating and refining investment strategies using market data." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203463" class="wp-caption-text">GIM advances agentic AI systems capable of independently generating and improving investment decisions in real time. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s platform is designed around what it calls a &#8220;Visionary Machine.&#8221; The concept allows AI agents to generate investment </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/hypothesis" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">hypotheses</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, test market assumptions and improve future decisions through measurable market outcomes. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Every investment action creates new data that helps the system refine its reasoning over time. Founder and Chief Executive Officer Jiahao Xu said investment AI is entering a new phase. Rather than assisting analysts with information gathering, future systems will increasingly generate and validate investment opportunities independently. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He added that GIM is developing AI capable of reasoning across market signals and continuously improving through real-world experience. The company&#8217;s technology development focuses on two main areas. The first is foundation models specifically trained for financial markets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/rubrik-raises-375m-expand-uk-emea-operations/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Rubrik Raises £375M to Expand UK Operations and EMEA Presence</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Research Supports Commercial AI Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">GIM continues to invest heavily in research alongside product development. Its flagship research paper, CogAlpha, was accepted for presentation at the ACL 2026 main conference with an Oral recommendation. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s AI models are trained on financial time-series data to identify market patterns, predict potential returns and optimise portfolio strategies. These systems also support trading execution and liquidity management across different market environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Alongside research, GIM has started validating its AI-powered investment products across multiple asset classes. The company plans to expand these live deployments as its technology matures.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports Long-Term Vision for AI Investing</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its long-term strategy extends beyond institutional investment tools. The company also plans to develop accessible investment products that allow a broader range of users to benefit from self-improving AI systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This vision is built around what GIM describes as &#8220;Shared Prosperity.&#8221; The company believes future intelligent systems should create value that is widely accessible rather than concentrated among a limited group of institutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding brings together investors with experience across artificial intelligence, financial technology and global capital markets. Their backing will support continued innovation as GIM expands its AI infrastructure and commercial offerings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With fresh capital in place, GIM plans to accelerate product development, expand its engineering capabilities and strengthen the deployment of autonomous AI systems across modern investment markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gim-raises-us20-million-ai-investment-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">GIM Raises US$20 Million to Advance AI Investment Systems</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
