		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203450</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Ollama Raises Fresh Capital to Accelerate Open AI Growth Ollama has raised $65 million in a Series B funding round to strengthen its position in the growing open AI ecosystem.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ollama-raises-65m-expand-open-ai-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ollama Raises $65M to Expand Open AI Developer Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Ollama Raises Fresh Capital to Accelerate Open AI Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ollama has raised $65 million in a Series B funding round to strengthen its position in the growing open AI ecosystem. The round was led by Theory Ventures, with participation from Benchmark, 8VC, Y Combinator, Pace Capital, 49 Palms, GTMFund, and other investors. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The money will fund further product development, cloud expansion and hiring, according to the company. Co-founded by Jeffrey Morgan and Michael Chiang, Ollama is an open-source platform allowing developers to run large language models on local machines. Ollama is available on Mac, Windows and Linux. Developers also have the option to bring workloads into Ollama cloud without modification of workflows. That approach has helped it rise as one of the largest platforms to get into the game with open source models.</span></p>
<h2><b>Developer Adoption Continues to Surge</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ollama&#8217;s growth has accelerated over the past year. The platform now supports 8.9 million monthly active developers and more than 67,000 community-built integrations. Usage has doubled since January, with nearly one million new installations added every week. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also reports adoption across 85% of Fortune 500 organisations, including businesses operating in healthcare, finance, and government. Developers use Ollama to simplify AI deployment without sacrificing privacy or performance. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Models can run locally when hardware allows. Larger workloads automatically scale into Ollama&#8217;s cloud using the same </span><a href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/career-development/what-are-interfaces" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">interface</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The company also confirms that customer data is never used to train its AI models, making the platform attractive for regulated industries.</span></p>
<h2><b>Partnerships Strengthen the Open Model Ecosystem<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203454" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203454" class="size-full wp-image-203454" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-vibrant-_StXLjY9sV-KICZD_XXn4_w_vEdgdF6USKuUJqsKSPxJFg_cover.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing an open AI ecosystem with collaboration between developers, hardware systems, and cloud infrastructure." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203454" class="wp-caption-text">Ollama strengthens its ecosystem through partnerships, enabling developers to build and run open AI models across devices and cloud environments. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ollama has built partnerships with many of the world&#8217;s leading AI model developers. These include Meta, Google DeepMind, Mistral, and MiniMax. The company also collaborates with hardware providers including NVIDIA, Intel, AMD, and Qualcomm. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These relationships give developers early access to new models and improved hardware performance. Chief Executive Officer Jeffrey Morgan said open models should remain easy to build with and available wherever developers choose to work. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He said the company remains committed to supporting its open-source community. Morgan added that the future of AI will depend on open models running across local devices and cloud environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Theory Ventures General Partner Tomasz Tunguz believes platforms like Ollama will become essential infrastructure for the next generation of AI software. He said more professionals are building their own AI-powered workflows, creating growing demand for accessible development platforms. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/super-com-raises-65m-series-d-to-expand-ai-powered-savings-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Super.com Raises $65M Series D to Expand AI-Powered Savings Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>New Investment Positions Ollama for Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B funding gives Ollama additional resources to expand its cloud computing footprint and continue improving its developer tools. The company also plans to hire key talent across engineering and product teams. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Those investments should assist Ollama in managing the rising interest of its services, particularly among enterprise clients, alongside that of independent developers. Millions of users and leading venture financiers behind it make Ollama ripe for future success.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many of these companies have been increasingly prioritizing the use of AI platforms, and are currently seeking options which offer them greater flexibility, reduced operating expenses and enhanced data privacy. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ollama’s Hybrid approach supports those desires as developers utilize the platform locally and in the cloud when the occasion arises, and the company has cultivated an ever-growing community around its open AI platform, by providing that flexibility.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ollama-raises-65m-expand-open-ai-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ollama Raises $65M to Expand Open AI Developer Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
