		<category><![CDATA[QuantumDiamonds]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Series A]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203434</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>German deeptech startup QuantumDiamonds has raised €91 million in its latest funding round. QuantumDiamonds announced that its latest capital comes from a €15 million Series A equity round and an</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantumdiamonds-has-raised-91m-semiconductor-testing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Chip Testing Startup QuantumDiamonds Has Raised €91m To Speed Up Manufacturing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">German deeptech startup QuantumDiamonds has raised €91 million in its latest funding round. QuantumDiamonds </span><a href="https://www.qd-st.com/press/series-a" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">announced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> that its latest capital comes from a €15 million Series A equity round and an additional €76 million in non-dilutive state aid.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As demand for AI chips surges, QuantumDiamonds will use the new capital to scale its quantum-driven semiconductor testing technology. The capital will help the German manufacturer avoid the struggle of improving production yields that other AI hardware manufacturers are facing. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">QuantumDiamonds says the capital injection will help build an advanced testing facility in Germany. The startup also plans to more than double its engineering workforce over the next twelve months to meet rising international demand.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From University Labs To a €91 Million Influx</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203437" style="width: 706px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203437" class="size-full wp-image-203437" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/QuantumDiamonds-team.jpg" alt="A large group photograph of the QuantumDiamonds team standing outside a modern building with a glass facade and a prominent &quot;76&quot; building number." width="696" height="392" /><p id="caption-attachment-203437" class="wp-caption-text">QuantumDiamonds Team</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">QuantumDiamonds began in 2022 as a spin-out from the famed Technical University of Munich (TUM). The company quickly grew from an academic research project into a top commercial player within the global deeptech ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The recent financial milestone has two unique parts. Climatetech venture firm World Fund led the €15 million equity round. Regional VC Bayern Kapital also participated alongside existing institutional investors including IQ Capital, Earlybird and First Momentum.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The remaining €76 million comes via non-dilutive state aid. Formally approved by the European Commission, the German Federal Ministry for Economic Affairs and the Free State of Bavaria provided this substantial grant. This capital allows the company to scale its infrastructure without diluting the equity of its founding team.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvidia-chip-challenger-sambanova-raises-1-billion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>NVIDIA Chip Challenger SambaNova Raises $1 Billion</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Building for Next-Generation Chip Inspection</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203436" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203436" class="size-large wp-image-203436" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/QuantumDiamonds-quantum-chip-testing-1024x593.jpg" alt="QuantumDiamonds quantum chip testing equipment utilizing green laser optics and advanced quantum sensing technology in a laboratory setting." width="1024" height="593" /><p id="caption-attachment-203436" class="wp-caption-text">Quantum Chip Testing Tech. Image Credit: QuantumDiamonds</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modern silicon microchips are incredibly complex. They use hundreds of chemically and physically precise layers in chip production. One defect can spoil an entire batch of silicon wafers, leaving billions of dollars to be lost in wasted materials and delayed product shipments for global chip manufacturers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">QuantumDiamonds solves this heavy industry bottleneck by utilizing quantum sensing technology. It integrates quantum sensors into unique inspection equipment to analyze chips on the atomic level. This non-destructive testing technique is able to reveal imperfections in the structure that are completely missed by the optical and electron microscopes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Early detection of structural defects in the manufacturing process means semiconductor manufacturers have time to quickly make changes to their machines. This significantly lowers the amount of manufacturing waste and speeds up the time response taken to ship new hardware.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/fleek-raises-25m-ebay-ai-secondhand-fashion-marketplace/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Fleek Raises $25M To Build AI Secondhand Fashion Marketplace</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Anchoring European Semiconductor Sovereignty</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The €76 million state grant directly supports the strategic goals of the </span><a href="https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/european-chips-act" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">EU Chips Act</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Europe is currently pushing to decrease its heavy reliance on foreign semiconductor supply chains based in Asia and North America.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The newly approved Munich facility serves as a cornerstone for this regional effort. As part of the state funding agreement, QuantumDiamonds will collaborate directly with European research universities and local small businesses. This open framework builds a robust local semiconductor infrastructure on European soil.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">QuantumDiamonds is quickly expanding its international footprint. The startup already employs 70 people. It has also successfully deployed its equipment inside active semiconductor fabs across Taiwan and the United States.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to CEO and co-founder Kevin Berghoff, major chipmakers view this quantum diagnostic platform as an essential tool for next-generation hardware. The company is now focused on accelerating mass production of its testing machinery in Munich to support its expanding list of international clients across the world&#8217;s primary technology hubs.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quaise-energy-raises-134-million-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Quaise Energy Raises $134M Series B Funding Round</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantumdiamonds-has-raised-91m-semiconductor-testing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Chip Testing Startup QuantumDiamonds Has Raised €91m To Speed Up Manufacturing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
