		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203419</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>One of NVIDIA’s biggest competitors just got a major boost. At the Raise Summit in Paris, it was announced that SambaNova raises $1 billion in a Series F funding round.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvidia-chip-challenger-sambanova-raises-1-billion/" data-wpel-link="internal">NVIDIA Chip Challenger SambaNova Raises $1 Billion At $11 Billion Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of NVIDIA’s biggest competitors just got a major boost. At the Raise Summit in Paris, it was </span><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tbjYLQWiNbc" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">announced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> that SambaNova raises $1 billion in a Series F funding round. The California-based AI chip startup SambaNova now has a valuation of $11 billion after its latest funding round. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This cash injection will help SambaNova solidify itself in the AI chip marketplace as tech firms and global investors are looking for real alternatives to Nvidia’s dominant market monopoly. The funding will help SambaNova scale and possibly shake up the chip market.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Behind the Massive $1 Billion Funding Round</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203421" style="width: 585px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203421" class="size-full wp-image-203421" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/SambaNova-Founder.jpeg" alt="Rodrigo Liang, co-founder and CEO of SambaNova Systems, smiling while holding up a square silicon AI microchip in front of a SambaNova DataScale server rack." width="575" height="347" /><p id="caption-attachment-203421" class="wp-caption-text">Rodrigo Liang. SambaNova Founder</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The massive financing round was led by prominent global growth investor General Atlantic. It also saw major financial participation from elite institutions like Seligman Ventures, T. Rowe Price Associates, and Capital Group. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The list of big-name backers did not stop there either. Existing and new investors like BlackRock, Intel Capital, and the Qatar Investment Authority also proudly joined the cap table. SambaNova plans to deploy this fresh capital right away. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They want to scale up their global enterprise deployments and aggressively expand their production capacity. Money will also go directly into upgrading their full-stack AI infrastructure, custom hardware systems, and advanced software layers. This financial strength gives them a massive runway.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/fleek-raises-25m-ebay-ai-secondhand-fashion-marketplace/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Fleek Raises $25M To Build AI Secondhand Fashion Marketplace</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifting the Focus to Cost-Effective AI Inference</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203422" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203422" class="size-large wp-image-203422" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/SambaNova-1024x570.jpg" alt="The SambaNova SN50 chip, engineered specifically to handle high-performance agentic AI inference workloads." width="1024" height="570" /><p id="caption-attachment-203422" class="wp-caption-text">SN50 AI Inference Chip. Image Credit: SambaNova</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For years, the tech world focused almost entirely on training massive artificial intelligence models. That training process requires insane amounts of energy and raw processing power. However, SambaNova is betting its future on a different phase of the model lifecycle called inference. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Inference is the computational process where an AI model actually responds to everyday user queries. As conversational AI agents become everyday tools for tasks like programming and emailing, inference demand is exploding. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SambaNova designs custom chips tailored specifically to handle these operational tasks quickly and cheaply. Their systems give companies a highly cost-effective choice compared to Nvidia’s rare and expensive graphic processors. Every token generated costs real money, making efficiency vital.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quaise-energy-raises-134-million-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Quaise Energy Raises $134M Series B Funding Round</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Securing JPMorgan Chase as a Core Partner</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The historic funding news arrived right alongside a massive corporate win for the startup. Banking giant JPMorgan Chase has officially selected SambaNova as its key inference infrastructure partner. The Wall Street powerhouse plans to deploy SambaNova’s advanced SN40 and SN50 systems directly inside its own secure facilities. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Financial institutions care deeply about strict data privacy, regulatory compliance, and ultra-low latency. By running these dedicated server units on-premises, JPMorgan maintains complete control over its sensitive financial data. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This major customer signing proves that top-tier enterprises are moving well past the initial AI hype cycle. They want practical systems that work flawlessly right now. Other banks are watching this rollout closely.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Breaking the Nvidia Market Monopoly</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NVIDIA currently rules the AI chip sector with an iron fist, making it one of the largest companies globally. Yet tech giants and corporate enterprises are desperate for diversified supply chains. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SambaNova’s co-founder and CEO, Rodrigo Liang, firmly stated that their new valuation reflects genuine market performance rather than empty investor hype. The company’s ongoing relationship with Intel also deepens their competitive reach. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Intel recently expanded its equity stake in the startup to help deliver inference solutions to rising AI-native companies. With billions in capital and elite Wall Street customers on board, SambaNova is proving that Nvidia won’t hold the crown forever. The AI hardware race is heating up rapidly.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/proxima-fusion-secures-411m-funding-google-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Proxima Fusion Secures €411M To Build Europe’s Fusion Power</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvidia-chip-challenger-sambanova-raises-1-billion/" data-wpel-link="internal">NVIDIA Chip Challenger SambaNova Raises $1 Billion At $11 Billion Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
