					<description><![CDATA[<p>The secondhand clothing industry is massive, with approximately $242 billion. It is often overlooked. Because its back-end infrastructure has remained stuck in the past. The secondhand clothing industry still relies</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fleek-raises-25m-ebay-ai-secondhand-fashion-marketplace/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fleek Raises $25M From eBay To Build AI Secondhand Fashion Marketplace</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The secondhand clothing industry is massive, with approximately </span><a href="https://www.persistencemarketresearch.com/market-research/second-hand-apparel-market.asp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">$242 billion</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. It is often overlooked. Because its back-end infrastructure has remained stuck in the past. The secondhand clothing industry still relies on slow, paper-based, and manual methods. London startup Fleek wants to fix that. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fleek raises $25m from eBay and Vinted’s early backer to speed up the rollout of its AI-powered B2B marketplace. The goal is to digitize the messy supply chains that move vintage and used clothes across global borders every single day.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strong Investor Backing from Industry Giants</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203407" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203407" class="size-full wp-image-203407" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/1783471995020.jpeg" alt="Fleek co-founders celebrate a major milestone after raising $25 million in Series B funding to scale their wholesale secondhand clothing platform." width="800" height="1000" /><p id="caption-attachment-203407" class="wp-caption-text">Fleek Secures $25M. Image Credit: Abhi Arora</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fleek just </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7480527178284175361/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">announced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> that it has raised $25 million in its Series B funding round. This round will increase the total value of funds raised by Fleek to $45 million. The Series B investment was led by Burda Principal Investments. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Interestingly, Burda was an early backer of Vinted, so they know exactly how to scale a resale platform into an 8-billion-euro company. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Burda was also among the initial investors in Vinted, which means they know how to grow a resale company into an €8 billion business. E-commerce giant eBay also joined the round, alongside FJ Labs and H14. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Existing heavyweights like Andreessen Horowitz, HV Capital, and Y Combinator stepped up to invest again. This fundraising shows that investor interest is changing. Instead of funding yet another consumer thrift app, venture firms are betting on the wholesale infrastructure that keeps the entire resale market running safely.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News:</i></b> <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quaise-energy-raises-134-million-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Quaise Energy Raises $134M Series B Funding Round</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">How Fleek Sort Digitizes Used Clothing</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The business was started in 2021 by co-founders Abhi Arora and Sanket Agarwal. At the core of their platform is a proprietary tool, Fleek Sort. It is a custom vision-language model trained on millions of secondhand transactions over the past four years. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Right now, sorting used garments is a slow, painful task. Workers in warehouses across India, Pakistan, and Dubai check every shirt and jacket by hand. Fleek Sort shifts this to digital. Graders can snap a smartphone photo or shoot a short video to instantly identify, tag, and grade items. The AI turns a complex physical process into a quick digital workflow.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlocking a Fragmented Global Resale Market</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203408" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203408" class="size-large wp-image-203408" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/pexels-burst-374677-1024x576.jpg" alt="A shopper searches through curated racks of vintage apparel at a local secondhand clothing boutique." width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-203408" class="wp-caption-text">Thrifting for Secondhand Clothing: Image Credit: Pexels</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Today’s secondhand clothing industry is enormous and worth well over $240 billion. About 24 billion used things are dropped into used goods bins in Western cities and then sorted worldwide each year. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, the system is flawed. Unpredictable quality and no price transparency from suppliers. But Fleek steps in to fill that void. Today, more than 2,000 verified wholesale suppliers are linked to more than 50,000 independent retailers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fleek has extended the useful life of 12 million products and avoided 13 billion liters of water and 23,000 tonnes of CO2 waste.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/proxima-fusion-secures-411m-funding-google-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Proxima Fusion Secures €411M To Build Europe’s Fusion Power</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Future Engineering and Growth Plans</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new money is going to be used by Fleek on a few specific areas. The primary focus is on growing its engineering workforce and scaling its engineering technology. The company aims to engage the AI technology more deeply in its search, recommendations, and buyer discovery technologies. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They will also be rolling out additional automated pilots in the US, UK and Europe, further building out their supplier base. Fleek wants to help warehouses get some of their inventory off the shelves by providing them with improved tools. In the end, it will enable vintage stores to purchase goods with greater consistency without any unpleasant surprises.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/even-realities-raises-150m-to-expand-privacy-first-smart-glasses/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Even Realities Raises $150M To Expand Privacy-First Smart Glasses</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fleek-raises-25m-ebay-ai-secondhand-fashion-marketplace/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fleek Raises $25M From eBay To Build AI Secondhand Fashion Marketplace</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
