					<description><![CDATA[<p>Arkenstone Defense Raises $35M Seed Round Arkenstone Defense has emerged from stealth after raising $35 million in seed funding to simplify government contracting for commercial technology companies. The round was</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/arkenstone-defense-raises-35m-to-simplify-government-contracting/" data-wpel-link="internal">Arkenstone Defense Raises $35M to Simplify Government Contracting</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Arkenstone Defense Raises $35M Seed Round</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Arkenstone Defense has emerged from stealth after raising $35 million in seed funding to simplify government contracting for commercial technology companies. The round was led by J2 Ventures, with participation from Susa Ventures, Granite Hill Capital Partners and Artis Ventures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Menlo Park-based startup is building an operating system that helps businesses manage the complex operational requirements of selling to the U.S. government. Its platform combines workforce management, compliance, payroll, personnel security and accreditation into a single service.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief executive officer Peter Dixon said many venture-backed companies struggle to enter the defence market because procurement systems were never designed for modern technology startups.</span></p>
<h2><b>Platform Removes Barriers for Defence Technology Startups</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Government contracting requires companies to satisfy strict operational and regulatory standards before securing federal work. These include cybersecurity certifications, security clearances, audited payroll systems and compliance programmes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Arkenstone packages these requirements into one managed platform. Instead of building separate internal systems, companies can use its infrastructure to become operationally ready within months.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes founders should focus on developing technology instead of navigating government administration. Its platform supports businesses from their first federal opportunity through long-term government contracts.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Defence Spending Creates New Opportunity</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203410" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203410" class="size-full wp-image-203410" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Arkenstone-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI-powered defence technology, autonomous systems, and an integrated cybersecurity compliance platform supporting commercial innovation in modern defence infrastructure." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203410" class="wp-caption-text">Growing defence investment is creating new opportunities for commercial technology providers, with integrated AI, autonomous systems, and unified cybersecurity compliance platforms helping organisations meet evolving defence requirements more efficiently. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding arrives as demand for commercial technology within defence continues to grow. Annual Pentagon spending on acquisition now approaches $300B a year, creating a huge opportunity for startups engaged in robotics, autonomy, artificial intelligence and advanced manufacturing. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, not enough commercial companies have been awarded work through the Department of Defense in recent years – with many commercial enterprises discouraged from entry into defense sector by high compliance costs and the growing regulatory complexities. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perhaps the most challenging task has been achieving Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification Level 2. Estimates from some of the companies that hold the credential peg the cost at “ hundreds of thousands of dollars “ , as well as, “ years to achieve .”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform we are developing with Arkenstone provides its clients with integrated compliance within a “ platform, not multiple products ,” avoiding the complexity of dealing with multiple, discrete vendors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fore-biotherapeutics-raises-67-4-million-series-d/" data-wpel-link="internal">FORE Biotherapeutics Raises $67.4M to Advance BRAF Cancer Therapy</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Investors See Infrastructure Gap in Defence Innovation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is led by Peter Dixon and chief operating officer William Treseder, who has spent more than 15 years helping connect Silicon Valley companies with the U.S. defence sector through programmes including Hacking for Defense and the Marine Innovation Unit.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Treseder said many promising technologies fail to reach government customers because startups cannot build the required operational infrastructure quickly enough. &#8220;The Pentagon has made it clear that it wants more commercial innovation,&#8221; Dixon said. &#8220;The problem is that the procurement system wasn&#8217;t built for venture-backed startups.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More than two dozen defence technology companies already use Arkenstone&#8217;s platform. The company expects the new funding to expand its operations and support additional commercial businesses entering government markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Alexander Harstrick, managing partner and co-founder of J2 Ventures, said the startup addresses a longstanding gap between commercial innovation and government </span><a href="https://www.order.co/blog/procurement/define-procurement/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">procurement</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. He believes Arkenstone provides the missing infrastructure needed for commercial technology companies to compete at scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As governments increasingly seek private-sector innovation, platforms that simplify compliance and contracting could play a larger role in modernising defence procurement. Arkenstone aims to become the operational backbone that enables more commercial technologies to reach government customers faster.</span></p>
